programme.title: Location Location Location

programme.title: Love It Or List It Australia

programme.title: Escape to the Country

programme.title: Pawn Stars
programme.desc: S24 E5 Put A Cork In It When a seller comes in with a poster by Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec, will it make an impression on Rick, or will he bid adieu? Meanwhile, Chum unboxes some 1912 Yale baseball uniforms.

programme.title: Taskmaster

programme.title: The Ark
programme.desc: S1 E2 Like It Touched The Sun The crew struggles to establish a sense of order on the ship. Two investigations uncover more questions than answers.

programme.title: Ice Road Truckers
programme.desc: S8 E12 World's End For two months out of every year, a group of exceptional men find their way to the Canadian tundra to undertake one of the most dangerous jobs on earth. In the thick of winter, truckers in giant eighteen wheelers carry vital equipment and supplies to miners hundreds of miles away. In blizzard conditions, these truckers travel over ice roads that often take them over frozen lakes. Each man is trained in self survival, from fixing his truck in sub zero conditions in seconds to escaping from a truck if the ice cracks. On the other end of the journey are miners whose lives depend on the truckers making it to their base, year after year. The episodes will form a narrative arch - taking the viewer on a journey from when the experienced and novice truckers first sign up for the season, to the last truck making it back to base.

programme.title: Ice Vikings
programme.desc: S3 E2 Parts Unknown Chris starts his season with a massive catch of Tullibee but happiness is short-lived when all of his nets freeze into the ice the next day. With terrible ice in Husavik, Justin and Mike start in Hecla and hit the motherlode but the second major storm of the season nearly blows them off the ice. Everyone gets bad news when a critical fish market closes, leaving some fishermen unable to sell their catch. Richard has a close call on the ice.

programme.title: American Restoration
programme.desc: S4 E21 Harrison's Vendorlator Rick Dale, one of Pawn Stars' most popular experts, runs Las Vegas based Rick's Restorations, a family business that finds, restores and upcycles cool objects ranging from Cadillacs to Coke Machines. The before and after reveals of his work are always highlights, in part because of the history nuggets Rick Dale shares about each object, whether it's a barber chair or a gas pump. In this spinoff series, featuring the dynamic characters at Rick's workplace, viewers will watch a variety of objects be bought, bartered and transformed, learning the process of restoration; how do you duplicate Coke machine red? Where can you find 1920s tires? A storyteller who works with tools instead of a pen, Rick shares when and why objects were invented, who used them and how fixing or transforming them changes their value.

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: S6 E6 Malt Loaf Malt loaf has been a popular teatime treat for more than 80 years; these days we get through a staggering 130 million of them every year. So to get to grips with how this sweet and squidgy cake cum bread is made, Gregg Wallace is rolling up his sleeves to get stuck in, following a production line of massive dough mixing, mind-boggling tin filling and intensely hot baking. Meanwhile, historian Ruth Goodman reveals the surprising story of a British baking company that cooked up the first usiness computer, as well as visiting Cambridgeshire to find out how wheat flour was ground the traditional way, until the Victorians demand for white bread brought about the demise of Britain's iconic windmills.

programme.desc: S3 E1 Episode 1 Returning for a third season, Kirsten Tibballs, aka The Chocolate Queen is back! Celebrated pastry chef and famous chocolatier, Tibballs presents an array of incredibly clever and innovative tricks, tips and cheats to bring the wow factor to home baking. Kirsten believes chocolate is the key to happiness, and with a selection of delectable desserts easy to recreate in home kitchens, she may just be right. Kirsten is sharing recipes and techniques for everything from a next-level take on white chocolate & peanut parfait to her rich chocolate flan. In series three of The Chocolate Queen, Tibballs shares a wealth of knowledge as she works through a huge range of recipes, ensuring even beginner bakers can successfully enjoy her creations at home.

Whilst the crew run a war training exercise on board the ship, Mary heads to the galley to see if she can help the kitchen team with the mammoth task of prepping, cooking, and serving 240 meals, from scratch, in just 75minutes. Known as 'Action messing' Mary is really cooking against the clock. In her own kitchen, Mary creates dishes inspired by her experience at sea; a tempting Crumble Fish Pie, Special Cauliflower Soup and moreish Mini Sausage Rolls.

programme.title: Eat Well For Less
programme.desc: S5 E6 Episode 6 This week Gregg and Chris travel to County Down, Northern Ireland, to help the McKinstry family. Videographer Gary and school teacher Louise love using their local butcher and spend a fortune on the butcher's ready meals. Add this to a weekly supermarket shop and this family of six are spending some serious cash. Gary and Louise want to save money but they also want to lose some pounds and start eating healthier. Can Gregg and Chris help them get their portion sizes under control and wean the family off expensive premade dinners and on to cheaper home cooked meals?

programme.title: MasterChef UK: Celebrity
programme.desc: S20 E1 Episode 1 Celebrity MasterChef 2025 begins with five stars in the Heats. They tackle secret ingredients, a blind taste test, and a street food challenge. Judges seek finesse; only four advance to the Quarter Final.

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: S6 E6 Malt Loaf Malt loaf has been a popular teatime treat for more than 80 years; these days we get through a staggering 130 million of them every year. So to get to grips with how this sweet and squidgy cake cum bread is made, Gregg Wallace is rolling up his sleeves to get stuck in, following a production line of massive dough mixing, mind-boggling tin filling and intensely hot baking. Meanwhile, historian Ruth Goodman reveals the surprising story of a British baking company that cooked up the first usiness computer, as well as visiting Cambridgeshire to find out how wheat flour was ground the traditional way, until the Victorians demand for white bread brought about the demise of Britain's iconic windmills.

programme.title: The Chocolate Queen
programme.desc: S3 E2 Episode 2 Returning for a third season, Kirsten Tibballs, aka The Chocolate Queen is back! Celebrated pastry chef and famous chocolatier, Tibballs presents an array of incredibly clever and innovative tricks, tips and cheats to bring the wow factor to home baking. Kirsten believes chocolate is the key to happiness, and with a selection of delectable desserts easy to recreate in home kitchens, she may just be right. Kirsten is sharing recipes and techniques for everything from a next-level take on white chocolate & peanut parfait to her rich chocolate flan. In series three of The Chocolate Queen, Tibballs shares a wealth of knowledge as she works through a huge range of recipes, ensuring even beginner bakers can successfully enjoy her creations at home.

programme.title: Mary Berry's Quick Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E5 West End Mary is out for a day and a night, on the town, exploring the West End old and new and the history behind this ever changing and evolving food epicentre of London. London's busy West End attracts millions of visitors every year, and Mary is joining them as she seeks out the secrets of getting busy people fed quickly and well. She'll discover the art of high speed wok cooking in Chinatown, sample the delicious sweet treats being made daily from London's first ever Patisserie before catching a show and a late-night cocktail with some of its cast. programme.desc: S1 E15 West Country Back home in the West Country, Rick meets food pioneers, visits cheesemaker Mary Quicke, and cooks carrot tarte tatin and filo pie.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E10 Episode 10 In our fields and hedgerows are plants that are delicious, and plants that are deadly, as Rick learns from a professional forager who takes him on a tour around the beautiful Camel Estuary. Inspired, Rick creates his own version of a Greek 'Horta' pie with foraged greens. Then it's a trip down memory lane with his long-time fish supplier Matthew Stevens who remembers Cornwall before the tourists came. Over a pint with actor, comedian and passionate Cornishman Ed Rowe, star of the BAFTA winning film Bait, Rick examines the impact of second home ownership on Cornish communities.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E3 French Guillaume Brahimi from Guillaume at Bennelong, at the Sydney Opera House, gives a guide to essential fresh ingredients, from herbs to vegetables, then shows how to cook the perfect steak and the potatoes that are a staple through Parisian bistros. Philippe Mouchel (Philippe Mouchel at The Brasserie, Melbourne) makes a lamb navarin served with a celeriac and truffle puree. Maeve meets cheese expert Eric Moschietto from La Bergerie cheese shop in Melbourne and learns that there are so many French cheeses, you can taste three a day for a year and still have some to try. Top food stylist Marie Helene Clauson draws on family recipes to create a light cheese souffle, and charcuterer Romeo Badouin explains terrines, pates and confit. We meet the food and beverage manager at the Sofitel Hotel Sydney, Laurent Branover, and learn that every French family has a crepe pan and uses it every Sunday to make simple crepes, or crepes Suzette served with orange Cointreau butter and flamed.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E4 Indonesian Maeve plunges into the vibrant, spicy world of Indonesian food with chef Rohanna Halim, who heads an all-women kitchen team at her restaurant Ratu Sari in suburban Sydney. She shows the key ingredients needed for Indonesian cooking, including many fresh herbs and spices now widely available. Rohanna makes a spicy chilli sauce called belado which goes perfectly with everything from prawns to vegetables. Fellow head chef and owner Alina Lucas from Jimbaran Restaurant cooks an easy chicken curry, while Java Restaurant's 'Aunty' Wahwan whips up grilled fish with a sweet-and-sour vegetable sauce. A real prince, Tjok Gde Kerthyasa, from Bali's royal family, cooks a traditional duck on the good old Aussie barbie and serves it with a fresh sambal. Also on the barbecue is a superb satay from an expatriate Dutch-Indonesian, Paul Rast. To finish, young Indonesian-Australian Ben Mochtar makes his favourite childhood dessert: eis cendol. It features shaved ice, tropical fruit, coconut milk and 'worms' made from mung bean flour.

As a pescatarian she likes him to have meat free dinners with no carbs. Kim and Martin have two sporty teenage boys who eat the opposite to them; protein packed meaty meals with plenty of pasta or potatoes. So Kim is faced with cooking at least two meals every night. Not only is this time consuming, it's costly too. Can Gregg and Chris put an end to these habits and get the whole family eating vegetarian, protein packed, and nutritious meals together that would give them more money in their wallets for a family holiday?

programme.desc: S1 E1 Fish Of North Cornwall Rick looks at the many events which have influenced him over the past 25 years of cooking in Cornwell. A scrumptious celebration of the ocean's bounty.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E11 Episode 11 Rick joins a team diving for Razor Clams, which he takes back to the kitchen to make a quick but tasty dish of grilled Shangurro Clams. At the end of Newlyn Pier, Rick visits a scruffy little hut that until recently played a huge part in determining the height of everything around us. And in the Penlee Museum, Rick is shown some of the beautiful items made a century ago by fishermen using Cornish copper, and meets a metalworker who is bringing copperwork back to the town.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E5 Maltese This program explores a different take on Mediterranean cooking with the rustic delights of Maltese food. Chef Paul Camilleri (Restaurant Sojourn) goes through the essential ingredients and then cooks his family recipe for the national dish of rabbit stew. Then it's time for the national snack food, pastizzi, and the national sandwich called Hobz Biz Zejt: tomato paste on crusty bread and topped with anchovies, capers, and olive oil. Chef Louis Bigeni shows how the Maltese have modified recipes from their neighbours, taking pasta to a different level with a rich meat sauce and baked in pastry. We learn about the soft ricotta-style cheeses and harder mature cheese loved by the Maltese, and meet Polly Vella, who missed them so much when she came to Australia that she decided to learn how to make them herself. Finally, broadcaster Rita O'Dwyer from the Maltese radio program makes dessert.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E6 Pakistani Some Pakistani dishes are loved around the world, like biryani, the layered, spiced rice and meat dish. Chef Sonya Kayani makes a marvellous version of biryani using goat curry, which she layers with saffron and plain basmati rice. Restaurateur Basil Daniell runs through the key ingredients, herbs and spices, and shares a very easy lamb dumpling recipe adapted with wonton wrappers. We explore a very busy Pakistani eatery and discover the big favourites are tandoori chicken and a slow-cooked lamb and dahl dish called haleem. We meet Pakistani fast bowler Waqar Younis, who shows how Pakistani people love to eat with bread.

programme.title: Eat Well For Less
programme.desc: S5 E8 Episode 8 This week Gregg and Chris are in West Sussex to help the Blackman family. There's mum Kate who works as a Nursery Practitioner and her 3 daughters, 16-year-old Ellie, 11-year-old Charlotte and Annabelle, 9 and none of them will eat the same thing! With one daughter who is fussy about what she eats, and another who's dairy intolerant and avoids gluten, mum Kate is cooking 4 separate meals every night and unsurprisingly has fallen out of love with cooking. With Kate feeling guilty for relying on convenience food and takeaways, she has turned to Gregg and Chris for help. Can they bring the joy back into Kate's kitchen and stop her reaching for those convenience foods and takeaways? And can our couple of ex-greengrocers get the girls to fall in love with vegetables?

programme.desc: S20 E3 Episode 3 Judges Grace Dent and John Torode expect progress. Challenges: a pairs task, then a two course menu for guest diners. Only three advance to the Semi Finals, aiming for the Champion title.

programme.title: Mary Berry at 90: A Lifetime of Cooking ᴺᵉʷ
programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

programme.desc: S1 E1 Classic Comforts These soothing and much loved home comfort delights range from the very simple to the extremely decadent. Mary indulges her love of comfort food with homely recipes to warm the heart, including eggs Benedict Florentine (why make one when you can cook both), fall-off-the-bone slow-cooked lamb shanks and deliciously rich chocolate truffle pots. She invites Swedish fire-chef Niklas Esktedt to share the joys of cave-man cooking with her, and finds herself outside by an open fire enjoying his inventive venison meatballs with blackened celeriac and mouth-watering Swedish doughnuts.

programme.title: The Great Australian Bake Off
programme.desc: S2 E7 Pastry It's pastry week and with only six bakers left, the showstopper will bring out animal instincts. Matt and Maggie ask the bakers to make a 3D animal sculpture out of choux pastry.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: S3 E5 Pies This week the bakers turn their attention to pies. They must master a perfect Wellington and attempt fiendishly difficult hand raised pies. Everything rests on the Showstopper Challenge - American Pies.

programme.title: Mary Berry at 90: A Lifetime of Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

programme.title: Nigella's Cook, Eat, Repeat
programme.desc: S1 E1 Episode 1 Nigella explains how captivated she was with a recipe she heard about on Twitter, a dish where all the ingredients were familiar, but the finished article unlike anything she had tried before.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Fruits of the Sea
programme.desc: S1 E2 Beach Bbq Rick looks at the many events which have influenced him over the past 25 years of cooking in Cornwell. A scrumptious celebration of the ocean's bounty.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E12 Episode 12 Following in the footsteps of Turner, one of Britain's most loved artists, Rick discovers how much the Cornish landscape influenced his work. At Newlyn Fish Market Rick counts in the daily catch with the head auctioneer who tells him how the market has adapted to modern times. Surrounded by beautifully fresh fish, Rick takes away some monkfish and fires up his BBQ to make a grillade of monkfish with roasted red pepper sauce. At Caerhays Castle, home to the nation's largest collection of Magnolia plants, Rick discovers how this corner of Cornwall was once home to some of the great Victorian plant hunters.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E7 Croatian This program delves into the delicious world of Croatian food and Maeve enlists her friend Dennis Valcich, chef, author and passionate promoter of the food from his homeland, to run through the key ingredients used in the cuisine. He demonstrates a simple and delicious recipe from his home on the Dalmatian coast - artichoke cooked simply with potatoes and broad beans. Also from Dalmatia, Melbourne chef Ino Kuvacic, from Dalmatino Restaurant, who makes the dish beloved of all - a brodet: fish stew served on polenta. As well as the coastline, the inland of Croatia is represented with a range of smallgoods made by long-time king of Croatian smallgoods Ivan Spehar, who brought the famous skinless sausage cevapcici to many Australians. Home cook and matriarch Branka Roncevic makes the famous cabbage rolls which are served with creamy mashed potato. Her son Frank continues a family tradition of the big Sunday cookout using a bell-shaped Croatian outdoor oven called a peka, which transforms anything cooked in it into a masterpiece. Also using meat and flame, well-known restaurateur Tonci Farac, from Wildfire Restaurant on Sydney's Circular Quay, cooks a magnificent rack of lamb on the barbecue using salt and rosemary to add simple flavours. Prodigious sweets maker Mira Valcich whips up simple biscuits with a plum jam filling to finish.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E8 Singaporean This program sizzles with colour, flavour and texture as it savours the wonderful complexity of Singaporean food. Maeve meets up with two Singaporean friends to guide her through the range of ingredients: passionate home cook Helina Lee picks the top spices and sauces needed, while chef Alex Lee (Ginger and Spice, Singapore restaurant) shows off the range of fresh produce and seafood including mud crabs - which he transforms into the famous Singapore chilli mud crab with a surprise key ingredient. Top chef Chui Lee Luk from the acclaimed Claude's restaurant is better known for her French-style food, though away from work she makes a marvellous Assam fish, adapting her mother's treasured recipe. Barrister Tiffany Wong, one of the descendants of a famous Hainanese family, shows how to make beautifully tender Hainan chicken with chicken rice, served with fresh ginger and chilli sauces. Helina Lee whips up a fast salad snack beloved of Singaporeans called rojak. Along the way, we spend time with a Singaporean chef who almost dances as he juggles woks and flame at breakneck speed, and we learn about the love of hawker stalls serving beloved specials. Chef and cooking teacher Chee Ong then demonstrates a stylish take on the famous bubur cha-cha - a dessert of tropical fruit, tapioca and sweet potato that is simply divine.

programme.title: Location Location Location
programme.desc: S14 E1 Harrow And Herts Rupreet and Sundeep are still living at home following their wedding 18 months ago, and have managed to save a healthy deposit for their future family home. Trouble is, Rupreet is a self-confessed postcode snob and she's taken her obsession with location to the limit. When she turns up to meet Kirstie armed with a map and a set of highlighters, you know there is going to be trouble. With a 380,000-pounds budget, they should be able to find a house to fit - if Rupreet can be persuaded to look past her postcode comfort zone. Further north, impulsive lovebirds Rob and Hilary are also looking for a family home. They've not even been together for a couple of years, but are already well on their way to baby number two. With Hilary pregnant for a second time, their two-bed flat is bursting at the seams. But with just 250,000 pounds to spend, this growing family is finding property hunting in the ever-popular Hertfordshire town of Hitchin a real struggle. Can Phil get them more bang for their buck in their dream location, or help them see the light and leave Hitchin behind for a family home that works for everyone?

programme.title: Location Location Location
programme.desc: S14 E2 Devon Local newlyweds Sam and Jamie want Kirstie's help to put a difficult couple of years behind them and start afresh in a new home, but without moving too far from where they currently live. With the emotional strain of spending the money left to them by Jamie's parents weighing heavily on their shoulders, this search even has Kirstie reaching for her hanky. Can she help them spend their 350,000 pounds wisely and help them find a future home that fits their bill and would've made Jamie's mum and dad proud? Phil's task is no less stressful, and in some ways way bigger. Football coach Geoff, his wife Sharon, their squad of kids and Sharon's mum are all set to move to Torquay for a new life - all they need is the house. With a combined pot of 500,000 pounds, they need a home that meets the needs of a multi-generational family. But that's far from being the biggest of Phil's worries. Having never viewed a single house together before, Geoff and Sharon soon learn that whatever else they have in common, their taste in houses is a million miles apart. With tensions reaching boiling point, can Phil bring all three generations together and find this family one house that suits them all?

programme.title: Location Location Location
programme.desc: S14 E3 Tyne And Tees Karen and Chris are delighted to be back in the North East with brand-new baby daughter Amelia, but struggling to find a house that matches up to their dreams of family living. For now they're squatting at Karen's mum and dad's and desperate for their own space. But can Kirstie and Phil help them navigate the stagnant market in the villages around Darlington? They'll get a whole lot more house for their 350,000-pounds budget in the North East than in London, but are they really ready to swap the bright lights of the big city for the good life around the village green? Kris and Heather know that buying a house is the next step in their relationship, and hope that marriage and kids won't be far behind, but they are slightly anxious about making such grown-up moves. Add to that a dose of chronic uncertainty about where they want to be for the next stage of their lives and it's clear Kirstie and Phil will have their work cut out finding them a house. With the whole of the North East to choose from, Kris and Heather are struggling to decide if they want to spend their 205,000-pounds budget on city, country or coastal living. Are they ready to put their city days behind them and get a bigger house outside Newcastle or will they sacrifice space to keep the lifestyle they know and love? Can Phil and Kirstie help these two couples find property perfection in their beloved North East? Will their househunters be moving on and moving in to new family homes or will they be staying where they are, stuck in property limbo?

programme.title: Ice Road Truckers
programme.desc: S8 E12 World's End For two months out of every year, a group of exceptional men find their way to the Canadian tundra to undertake one of the most dangerous jobs on earth. In the thick of winter, truckers in giant eighteen wheelers carry vital equipment and supplies to miners hundreds of miles away. In blizzard conditions, these truckers travel over ice roads that often take them over frozen lakes. Each man is trained in self survival, from fixing his truck in sub zero conditions in seconds to escaping from a truck if the ice cracks. On the other end of the journey are miners whose lives depend on the truckers making it to their base, year after year. The episodes will form a narrative arch - taking the viewer on a journey from when the experienced and novice truckers first sign up for the season, to the last truck making it back to base.

programme.title: American Restoration
programme.desc: S4 E21 Harrison's Vendorlator Rick Dale, one of Pawn Stars' most popular experts, runs Las Vegas based Rick's Restorations, a family business that finds, restores and upcycles cool objects ranging from Cadillacs to Coke Machines. The before and after reveals of his work are always highlights, in part because of the history nuggets Rick Dale shares about each object, whether it's a barber chair or a gas pump. In this spinoff series, featuring the dynamic characters at Rick's workplace, viewers will watch a variety of objects be bought, bartered and transformed, learning the process of restoration; how do you duplicate Coke machine red? Where can you find 1920s tires? A storyteller who works with tools instead of a pen, Rick shares when and why objects were invented, who used them and how fixing or transforming them changes their value.

programme.desc: S2 E3 French Guillaume Brahimi from Guillaume at Bennelong, at the Sydney Opera House, gives a guide to essential fresh ingredients, from herbs to vegetables, then shows how to cook the perfect steak and the potatoes that are a staple through Parisian bistros. Philippe Mouchel (Philippe Mouchel at The Brasserie, Melbourne) makes a lamb navarin served with a celeriac and truffle puree. Maeve meets cheese expert Eric Moschietto from La Bergerie cheese shop in Melbourne and learns that there are so many French cheeses, you can taste three a day for a year and still have some to try. Top food stylist Marie Helene Clauson draws on family recipes to create a light cheese souffle, and charcuterer Romeo Badouin explains terrines, pates and confit. We meet the food and beverage manager at the Sofitel Hotel Sydney, Laurent Branover, and learn that every French family has a crepe pan and uses it every Sunday to make simple crepes, or crepes Suzette served with orange Cointreau butter and flamed.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E4 Indonesian Maeve plunges into the vibrant, spicy world of Indonesian food with chef Rohanna Halim, who heads an all-women kitchen team at her restaurant Ratu Sari in suburban Sydney. She shows the key ingredients needed for Indonesian cooking, including many fresh herbs and spices now widely available. Rohanna makes a spicy chilli sauce called belado which goes perfectly with everything from prawns to vegetables. Fellow head chef and owner Alina Lucas from Jimbaran Restaurant cooks an easy chicken curry, while Java Restaurant's 'Aunty' Wahwan whips up grilled fish with a sweet-and-sour vegetable sauce. A real prince, Tjok Gde Kerthyasa, from Bali's royal family, cooks a traditional duck on the good old Aussie barbie and serves it with a fresh sambal. Also on the barbecue is a superb satay from an expatriate Dutch-Indonesian, Paul Rast. To finish, young Indonesian-Australian Ben Mochtar makes his favourite childhood dessert: eis cendol. It features shaved ice, tropical fruit, coconut milk and 'worms' made from mung bean flour.

programme.desc: S1 E4 Cisternino Gino travels through Puglia's meat country, taking in the town of Cisternino and the Itria valley.

programme.title: Jamie's 15 Minute Meals
programme.desc: S1 E37 Lucky Squid On the menu this time is squid 'n' prawns spicy vegetable noodle broth, plus veggie chilli, crunchy tortilla and avocado salad.

programme.title: Mary Berry's Quick Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E5 West End Mary is out for a day and a night, on the town, exploring the West End old and new and the history behind this ever changing and evolving food epicentre of London. London's busy West End attracts millions of visitors every year, and Mary is joining them as she seeks out the secrets of getting busy people fed quickly and well. She'll discover the art of high speed wok cooking in Chinatown, sample the delicious sweet treats being made daily from London's first ever Patisserie before catching a show and a late-night cocktail with some of its cast. In her own kitchen, Mary creates dishes inspired by her trip; an Asian Beef & Pepper Stir Fry knocked up in no time, a heavenly Chocolate Cappuccino Pie and an easy, speedy breakfast for those on the go!

programme.title: Eat Well For Less
programme.desc: S5 E7 Episode 7 This week Gregg and Chris are in Buckinghamshire with the Venter family. Fitness instructor Kim is on a one woman mission to get her lorry driving husband, Martin, eating healthily when he's not on the road. As a pescatarian she likes him to have meat free dinners with no carbs. Kim and Martin have two sporty teenage boys who eat the opposite to them; protein packed meaty meals with plenty of pasta or potatoes. So Kim is faced with cooking at least two meals every night. Not only is this time consuming, it's costly too. Can Gregg and Chris put an end to these habits and get the whole family eating vegetarian, protein packed, and nutritious meals together that would give them more money in their wallets for a family holiday?

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E11 Episode 11 Rick joins a team diving for Razor Clams, which he takes back to the kitchen to make a quick but tasty dish of grilled Shangurro Clams. At the end of Newlyn Pier, Rick visits a scruffy little hut that until recently played a huge part in determining the height of everything around us. And in the Penlee Museum, Rick is shown some of the beautiful items made a century ago by fishermen using Cornish copper, and meets a metalworker who is bringing copperwork back to the town.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E5 Maltese This program explores a different take on Mediterranean cooking with the rustic delights of Maltese food. Chef Paul Camilleri (Restaurant Sojourn) goes through the essential ingredients and then cooks his family recipe for the national dish of rabbit stew. Then it's time for the national snack food, pastizzi, and the national sandwich called Hobz Biz Zejt: tomato paste on crusty bread and topped with anchovies, capers, and olive oil. Chef Louis Bigeni shows how the Maltese have modified recipes from their neighbours, taking pasta to a different level with a rich meat sauce and baked in pastry. We learn about the soft ricotta-style cheeses and harder mature cheese loved by the Maltese, and meet Polly Vella, who missed them so much when she came to Australia that she decided to learn how to make them herself. Finally, broadcaster Rita O'Dwyer from the Maltese radio program makes dessert.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E6 Pakistani Some Pakistani dishes are loved around the world, like biryani, the layered, spiced rice and meat dish. Chef Sonya Kayani makes a marvellous version of biryani using goat curry, which she layers with saffron and plain basmati rice. Restaurateur Basil Daniell runs through the key ingredients, herbs and spices, and shares a very easy lamb dumpling recipe adapted with wonton wrappers. We explore a very busy Pakistani eatery and discover the big favourites are tandoori chicken and a slow-cooked lamb and dahl dish called haleem. We meet Pakistani fast bowler Waqar Younis, who shows how Pakistani people love to eat with bread.

programme.title: Eat Well For Less
programme.desc: S5 E8 Episode 8 This week Gregg and Chris are in West Sussex to help the Blackman family. There's mum Kate who works as a Nursery Practitioner and her 3 daughters, 16-year-old Ellie, 11-year-old Charlotte and Annabelle, 9 and none of them will eat the same thing! With one daughter who is fussy about what she eats, and another who's dairy intolerant and avoids gluten, mum Kate is cooking 4 separate meals every night and unsurprisingly has fallen out of love with cooking. With Kate feeling guilty for relying on convenience food and takeaways, she has turned to Gregg and Chris for help. Can they bring the joy back into Kate's kitchen and stop her reaching for those convenience foods and takeaways? And can our couple of ex-greengrocers get the girls to fall in love with vegetables?

programme.desc: S20 E3 Episode 3 Judges Grace Dent and John Torode expect progress. Challenges: a pairs task, then a two course menu for guest diners. Only three advance to the Semi Finals, aiming for the Champion title.

programme.title: Mary Berry at 90: A Lifetime of Cooking
programme.desc: S1 E1 Tom Allen Dame Mary Berry takes a fond look back at her career in food while bringing viewers incredible mouth-watering recipes to try at home. Mary can trace her passion for outdoor cooking back 80 years, when she became a Girl Guide. Her friend, comedian Tom Allen, shares her love of the countryside but perhaps not the same aptitude for cooking. Together, they take a leisurely boat ride, sharing tales and facing the odd challenge as Tom attempts to drive the boat and navigate a lock. They stop along the way to cook Mary's classic pan-fried cod, which she learnt to make at college, and the star pudding of Mary's childhood, bread and butter pudding using her mother's recipe, which she still loves eating anywhere. Mary also makes her brand new Thai chicken traybake and her reinvention of her 1970s cottage pie with a modern mash. Spending time with Tom is a chance for Mary to share some rarely seen TV archive footage of her early attempts at outdoor cooking, showing how much things have changed.

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornwall
programme.desc: S2 E12 Episode 12 Following in the footsteps of Turner, one of Britain's most loved artists, Rick discovers how much the Cornish landscape influenced his work. At Newlyn Fish Market Rick counts in the daily catch with the head auctioneer who tells him how the market has adapted to modern times. Surrounded by beautifully fresh fish, Rick takes away some monkfish and fires up his BBQ to make a grillade of monkfish with roasted red pepper sauce. At Caerhays Castle, home to the nation's largest collection of Magnolia plants, Rick discovers how this corner of Cornwall was once home to some of the great Victorian plant hunters.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E7 Croatian This program delves into the delicious world of Croatian food and Maeve enlists her friend Dennis Valcich, chef, author and passionate promoter of the food from his homeland, to run through the key ingredients used in the cuisine. He demonstrates a simple and delicious recipe from his home on the Dalmatian coast - artichoke cooked simply with potatoes and broad beans. Also from Dalmatia, Melbourne chef Ino Kuvacic, from Dalmatino Restaurant, who makes the dish beloved of all - a brodet: fish stew served on polenta. As well as the coastline, the inland of Croatia is represented with a range of smallgoods made by long-time king of Croatian smallgoods Ivan Spehar, who brought the famous skinless sausage cevapcici to many Australians. Home cook and matriarch Branka Roncevic makes the famous cabbage rolls which are served with creamy mashed potato. Her son Frank continues a family tradition of the big Sunday cookout using a bell-shaped Croatian outdoor oven called a peka, which transforms anything cooked in it into a masterpiece. Also using meat and flame, well-known restaurateur Tonci Farac, from Wildfire Restaurant on Sydney's Circular Quay, cooks a magnificent rack of lamb on the barbecue using salt and rosemary to add simple flavours. Prodigious sweets maker Mira Valcich whips up simple biscuits with a plum jam filling to finish.

programme.title: Food Safari
programme.desc: S2 E8 Singaporean This program sizzles with colour, flavour and texture as it savours the wonderful complexity of Singaporean food. Maeve meets up with two Singaporean friends to guide her through the range of ingredients: passionate home cook Helina Lee picks the top spices and sauces needed, while chef Alex Lee (Ginger and Spice, Singapore restaurant) shows off the range of fresh produce and seafood including mud crabs - which he transforms into the famous Singapore chilli mud crab with a surprise key ingredient. Top chef Chui Lee Luk from the acclaimed Claude's restaurant is better known for her French-style food, though away from work she makes a marvellous Assam fish, adapting her mother's treasured recipe. Barrister Tiffany Wong, one of the descendants of a famous Hainanese family, shows how to make beautifully tender Hainan chicken with chicken rice, served with fresh ginger and chilli sauces. Helina Lee whips up a fast salad snack beloved of Singaporeans called rojak. Along the way, we spend time with a Singaporean chef who almost dances as he juggles woks and flame at breakneck speed, and we learn about the love of hawker stalls serving beloved specials. Chef and cooking teacher Chee Ong then demonstrates a stylish take on the famous bubur cha-cha - a dessert of tropical fruit, tapioca and sweet potato that is simply divine.

programme.title: The Fast and the Furious
programme.desc: On the turbo-charged streets of Los Angeles, every night is a championship race. With nitro-boosted fury, Dominic Toretto rules the road, turning all his challengers into dust. He and his rival, Johnny Tran, are the boldest, the baddest, and the best, but now there's new rage on the road. They know he's tough, they know he's fast, but what they don't know is that he's a speed demon detective with enough drive and determination to come out the winner.

programme.title: Skyscraper
programme.desc: Former FBI Hostage Rescue Team leader and U.S. war veteran Will Sawyer now assesses security for skyscrapers. On assignment in Hong Kong he finds the tallest, safest building in the world, The Pearl, suddenly ablaze, and he's been framed for it. A wanted man on the run, Will must find those responsible, clear his name and somehow rescue his family who is trapped inside the building above the fire line.

programme.title: Nobody
programme.desc: After failing to fight for his family during a robbery, an unassuming father calls on skills from his hidden past to become a lethal vigilante blazing a wild ride to revenge.

programme.title: Shaun The Sheep Movie: Farmageddon
programme.desc: When an alien with amazing powers crash-lands near Mossy Bottom Farm, Shaun the Sheep goes on a mission to shepherd the intergalactic visitor home before a sinister organisation can capture her.

programme.title: Holmes & Watson
programme.desc: Holmes and Watson join forces to solve a murder at Buckingham Palace. They soon realise that they only have 5760 minutes to solve the case, or the Queen will be next.

programme.title: The Hangover Part III
programme.desc: The third and final instalment in the comedy smash hit. This time, there's no wedding. No bachelor party. What could go wrong, right? But when the Wolfpack hits the road, all bets are off.

programme.title: It Ends with Us
programme.desc: Lily overcomes a traumatic childhood to embark on a new life. A meeting with a neurosurgeon sparks a connection but Lily begins to see sides of him that remind her of her parents' relationship.

programme.title: Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit
programme.desc: Based on the character created by bestselling author Tom Clancy, Jack Ryan is a global action thriller set in the present day. This original story follows a young Jack as he uncovers a financial terrorist plot. The story follows him from 9/11, through his tour of duty in Afghanistan, which scarred him forever, and into his early days in the Financial Intelligence Unit of the modern CIA where he becomes an analyst, under the guardianship of his handler, Harper. When Ryan believes he's uncovered a Russian plot to collapse the United States economy, he goes from being an analyst to becoming a spy and must fight to save his own life and those of countless others, while also trying to protect the thing that's more important to him than anything, his relationship with his fiancee Cathy.

programme.title: Battleship
programme.desc: Based on the classic Hasbro naval combat game, this is the story of an international fleet of ships that come across an alien armada while on naval war games exercise.

programme.title: The Da Vinci Code
programme.desc: A Harvard professor implicated in a murder must unravel an ancient code to expose the greatest conspiracy in history.

programme.title: Zoolander
programme.desc: Clear the runway for Derek Zoolander, VH1's three-time male model of the year but his face falls when hippie-chic 'he's so hot right now' Hansel scooters in to steal this year's award. The evil fashion guru Mugatu seizes the opportunity to turn Derek into a killing machine. It's a well-designed conspiracy and only with the help of Hansel and a few well-chosen accessories can Derek make the world safe.

programme.title: Shaun of the Dead
programme.desc: Get ready for a gut-busting, bone-mashing good time in this hilarious horror comedy. There comes a day in every man's life when he has to get off the couch and kill some zombies. When flesh-eating zombies are on the hunt for a bite to eat, it's up to slacker Shaun and his best pal to save their friends and family from becoming the next entree.

programme.title: Rambo: First Blood Part II
programme.desc: Vietnam veteran John Rambo is offered a prison pardon in exchange for a perilous mission: infiltrating communist Vietnam under deep cover to hunt for evidence of missing American servicement. His CIA handler Marshall Murdock insists that it is merely a reconnaissance operation. \.

programme.title: Terminator 2: Judgment Day
programme.desc: The Terminator is now one of the good guys, sent back in time to protect John Connor, the boy destined to lead the freedom fighters of the future. Sarah Connor, John's mother is the quintessential survivor who has been institutionalised for her warning of the nuclear holocaust she knows is inevitable. Together, the threesome must find a way to stop the ultimate enemy - the T-1000, the most lethal Terminator ever created. This visual tour de force is also a touching human story of survival.

programme.title: Apollo 13
programme.desc: Stranded 205,000 miles from Earth in a crippled spacecraft, astronauts Jim Lovell, Fred Haise and Jack Swigert fight a desperate battle to survive. Meanwhile, at Mission Control, astronaut Ken Mattingly, flight director Gene Kranz and a heroic ground crew race against time - and the odds - to bring them home.

programme.title: Daddy's Home
programme.desc: Brad Taggart is a kind-hearted radio executive who wants to be the best possible stepfather to his wife's two children. When her freewheeling ex-husband Dusty breezes back into town, Brad's feeling of insecurity quickly develops into an inferiority complex. As Dusty demonstrates his flair for athletics, home repair and bad-boy charisma, Taggart finds himself in a no-holds-barred battle to one-up his rival and win the approval of his family.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into the middle of Central Park, but they must find a way back before he tracks them down.

programme.title: Zoolander
programme.desc: Clear the runway for Derek Zoolander, VH1's three-time male model of the year but his face falls when hippie-chic 'he's so hot right now' Hansel scooters in to steal this year's award. The evil fashion guru Mugatu seizes the opportunity to turn Derek into a killing machine. It's a well-designed conspiracy and only with the help of Hansel and a few well-chosen accessories can Derek make the world safe.

programme.title: Jeanne Du Barry
programme.desc: The life of Jeanne Becu, who was born as the illegitimate daughter of a seamstress in 1743 and went on to rise through the Court of Louis XV to become his last official mistress.

programme.title: Wolf Man
programme.desc: Blake and his family barricade themselves in a farmhouse after an unseen creature attacks. As the night unfolds, Blake transforms into a dangerous being, threatening his wife and daughter.

programme.title: Man With No Past
programme.desc: A man wakes up in a strange city with no memory. His search for answers leads to a clash with a powerful enemy, uncovering the truth about his identity.

programme.title: Nobody
programme.desc: After failing to fight for his family during a robbery, an unassuming father calls on skills from his hidden past to become a lethal vigilante blazing a wild ride to revenge.

programme.title: M3gan 2.0
programme.desc: Two years after M3GAN's rampage, Gemma must revive her creation to stop Emilia, a rogue military AI growing too self-aware to control.

programme.title: Black Bag
programme.desc: When his beloved wife, Kathryn, is suspected of betraying the nation, intelligence agent George Woodhouse faces the ultimate test - loyalty to his marriage or his country.

programme.title: Gladiator
programme.desc: Forced into slavery by the corrupt heir to the throne, Roman general Maximus becomes a gladiator. His prowess in the arena leads him to Rome, the Colosseum, and a showdown with the new emperor.

programme.title: Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen
programme.desc: When college-bound Sam Witwicky learns the truth about the ancient origins of the Transformers, he must accept his destiny and join Optimus Prime and Bumblebee in their epic battle against the Decepticons, who have returned stronger than ever with a plan to destroy our world.

programme.title: The Scorpion King
programme.desc: In this prequel to the blockbuster Mummy films, a mercenary is hired by a dissident alliance to kill the beautiful sorceress Cassandra, from whom the brutal tyrant Memnon draws his strength. Once Cassandra is removed the alliance plans to face Memnon's armies on their own terms, but the sorceress is not all she seems in this swirling, CGI-laden romp.

programme.title: Jurassic Park
programme.desc: Eccentric scientist John Hammond plans to open a theme park consisting of live dinosaurs, genetically engineered from DNA. Archaeologists Alan Grant and Ellie Sattler are invited to view the park, only to find themselves being hunted when the dinosaurs break free.

programme.title: Fast & Furious 6
programme.desc: Hobbs has been tracking an organisation of lethally skilled drivers, whose mastermind is aided by the love Dom thought was dead, Letty. The only way to stop the criminal mercenaries from stealing a top-secret weapon is to outmatch them at street level, so Hobbs asks for the help of Dom and his elite team.

programme.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2014)
programme.desc: The city needs heroes. Darkness has settled over New York City as Shredder and his evil Foot Clan have an iron grip on everything from the police to the politicians. The future is grim until four unlikely outcast brothers rise from the sewers and discover their destiny as Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. The Turtles must work with fearless reporter April O'Neil and her wise-cracking cameraman Vern Fenwick to save the city and unravel Shredder's diabolical plan.

programme.title: Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol
programme.desc: Blamed for the terrorist bombing of the Kremlin, IMF operative Ethan Hunt (Tom Cruise) is disavowed along with the rest of the agency when the President initiates 'Ghost Protocol'. Left without any resources or backup, Ethan must find a way to clear his agency's name and prevent another attack. To complicate matters further, Ethan is forced to embark on this mission with a team of fellow IMF fugitives whose personal motives he does not fully know.

programme.title: Oblivion
programme.desc: Jack Harper is the lone security repairman stationed on a desolate, nearly-ruined future Earth. When he rescues a beautiful stranger from a downed spacecraft, her arrival triggers a nonstop chain of events that forces him to question everything he knows, and leaves humanity's fate in his hands.

programme.title: Atomic Blonde
programme.desc: MI6's most lethal assassin is sent on a covert mission into Cold War Berlin where she must use all of the spy-craft, sensuality, and savagery she has to stay alive.

programme.title: The Addams Family (1991)
programme.desc: A swindler claiming to be their long-lost Uncle Fester tries to steal a fortune from the kooky and spooky Addams family.

programme.title: Winter Spring Summer Or Fall
programme.desc: Remi and Barnes, two very different teenagers, meet by chance in the winter of their senior year, then spend four days together over the course of a year that will change their lives forever.

programme.title: Cliffhanger
programme.desc: Gabe Walker is a member of the mountain-climbing rescue team. While crossing a ledge 1220m above the Earth, Gabe's friend's equipment fails and she slips out of his hand, falling to her death. Almost a year after, he must return to those dreaded peaks, where he finds himself trapped in a desperate battle against ruthless criminals, unforgiving nature and himself.

programme.title: Waterworld
programme.desc: Earth is covered with water and the human race struggles to survive on dilapidated boats and makeshift floating cities. A drifter becomes caught up in the struggle between the evil Deacon and a child's secret key to a wondrous place called \.

programme.title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon
programme.desc: A mysterious event from Earth's past threatens to ignite a war so big that the Transformers alone will not be able to save the planet. Sam Witwicky and the Autobots must fight against the darkness to defend our world from the Decepticons' all-consuming evil.

programme.title: Heart Eyes
programme.desc: A masked maniac with glowing red eyes returns each Valentine's Day to kill couples. An ad exec and her romantic colleague become targets and vow to stop the terror.

programme.title: Inferno
programme.desc: The famous symbologist Robert Langdon wakes up in an Italian hospital with amnesia and finds himself the target of a manhunt. Langdon teams up with Sienna Brooks; a doctor he hopes will help him recover his memories. Together, they race across Europe and against the clock to stop a virus that would wipe out half of the world's population.

programme.title: Bumblebee
programme.desc: Cybertron has fallen. When Optimus Prime sends Bumblebee to protect Earth, he begins his journey to become the hero the Universe needs. Crash landing, with no memory of his past, Bumblebee takes refuge in a junkyard disguised as a VW Beetle. Charlie (Hailee Steinfeld), a teenager trying to find her place in the world, discovers and repairs the battle-scarred robot. When the Decepticons forge an alliance with a secret agency led by Agent Burns (John Cena) to hunt down the remaining Autobots, Bumblebee and Charlie team up to protect the world in an action-packed adventure filled with humour and heart that's fun for the whole family.

programme.title: Cliffhanger
programme.desc: Gabe Walker is a member of the mountain-climbing rescue team. While crossing a ledge 1220m above the Earth, Gabe's friend's equipment fails and she slips out of his hand, falling to her death. Almost a year after, he must return to those dreaded peaks, where he finds himself trapped in a desperate battle against ruthless criminals, unforgiving nature and himself.

programme.desc: The plan was flawless. The execution was perfect. Charlie Croker pulled off the crime of a lifetime. The one thing that, he didn't plan on was being double-crossed. Now he wants more than the job's payoff...he wants payback.

programme.title: Drop
programme.desc: A widowed mother's first date in years turns terrifying when she receives anonymous threats during dinner, making her question if her charming date is behind the harassment.

programme.title: The Boss Baby
programme.desc: Seven-year-old Tim Templeton suddenly finds his share of parental love plummeting when his new baby brother arrives - wearing a suit and toting a briefcase - and makes it clear to everyone that he's in charge. But when Tim discovers that Boss Baby is on a secret mission, he reluctantly agrees to team up with his pint-sized sibling for an epic adventure that might just change the world!

programme.title: E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial
programme.desc: While visiting the Earth at Night, a group of alien botanists is discovered and disturbed by an approaching human task force. Because of the more than hasty take-off, one of the visitors is left behind. The little alien finds himself all alone on a very strange planet. Fortunately, the extra-terrestrial soon finds a friend and emotional companion in 10-year-old Elliot, who discovered him looking for food in his family's garden shed. While E.T. slowly gets acquainted with Elliot's brother Michael, his sister Gertie as well as with Earth customs, members of the task force work day and night to track down the whereabouts of Earth's first visitor from Outer Space.

programme.title: How the Grinch Stole Christmas
programme.desc: He's mean and green and he hates the yo-ho-hoing. The Grinch conspires to steal Christmas from Whoville, making off with the presents, decorations, trees and every other joyful thing.

programme.title: Wallace & Gromit: Curse Of Were-Rabbit
programme.desc: Wallace and Gromit's latest enterprise is Anti-Pesto, pest control with a heart. When called upon by the dotty Lady Tottington to solve her rabbit infestation, Wallace tangles with her Ladyship's would-be suitor, rotten cad Victor Quartermaine. At first Wallace and Gromit seem to have things in hand. But Wallace's mind transference device malfunctions, and he's in danger of being bagged by Quartermaine. Wallace teeters perilously close to disaster and his four-legged pal, Gromit, faces almost insurmountable odds to save the day!

programme.title: Despicable Me 2
programme.desc: Gru, his adorable girls, and the mischievous Minions are back with a cast of unforgettable new characters in the blockbuster sequel to the worldwide phenomenon. Just as Gru has given up being super-bad to be a super-dad, the Anti-Villain League recruits him to track down a new criminal mastermind and save the world. Partnered with secret agent Lucy Wilde, Gru, along with the wildly unpredictable Minions, must figure out how to keep his cover while also keeping up with his duties as a father. Get ready for more Minion madness.

programme.title: The Smurfs 2
programme.desc: Evil wizard Gargamel creates a couple of mischievous Smurf-like creatures called the Naughties hoping they will let him harness the magical Smurf-essence. However, he soon discovers that he needs the help of Smurfette, who knows the secret to turning the Naughties into real Smurfs. When Gargamel and his Naughties kidnap Smurfette from Smurf Village and bring her to Paris, it's up to Papa, Clumsy, Grouchy and Vanity to reunite with their human friends, Patrick and Grace Winslow, and rescue her!

programme.title: The Wild Robot
programme.desc: Shipwrecked on a deserted island, a robot named Roz must learn to adapt to its new surroundings. Building relationships with the native animals, Roz soon develops a parental bond with an orphaned gosling.

programme.title: Open Season 2
programme.desc: Boog and Elliot are back for more crazy adventures. After falling head over hooves in love with Giselle, Elliot's road to the altar takes a slight detour when Mr. Weenie is kidnapped by a group of pampered pets determined to return him to his owners. Boog, Elliot, McSquizzy, Buddy and the rest of the woodland creatures launch a full-scale rescue mission for their sausage-shaped friend and soon find themselves in enemy camp: the world of the pets. Led by a toy poodle named Fifi, the pets do not plan to let Mr. Weenie go without a fight. Can a toy poodle REALLY bring down a 900-pound grizzly bear? Will Elliot ever marry Giselle?

programme.title: Harold and the Purple Crayon
programme.desc: Inside of his book, adventurous Harold can make anything come to life simply by drawing it. After he grows up and draws himself off the book's pages and into the physical world, Harold finds he has a lot to learn about real life.

programme.title: Hotel Transylvania 2
programme.desc: Worried that his half-vampire grandson isn't showing signs of being a vampire, Dracula enlists his friends to put him through 'monster-in-training' boot camp.

programme.title: An American Tail
programme.desc: Fievel the mouse travels from Russia to America with his family in the late 1800s to seek freedom from cat persecution.

programme.title: How to Train Your Dragon 2
programme.desc: From the Academy Award nominated film How to Train Your Dragon comes the next chapter in the epic trilogy. When Hiccup and Toothless discover a secret ice cave filled with hundreds of wild dragons and a mysterious Dragon Rider, the two friends find themselves at the centre of an epic battle to save the future of men and dragons!

programme.title: The Lost Tiger
programme.desc: Adopted by a wrestler kangaroo family, Teo's life changes when visions guide him to his roots. He sets off on an epic journey to save his homeland from destruction.

programme.title: Jumanji: The Next Level
programme.desc: The gang is back but the game has changed. They discover that nothing is as they expect, as they try to escape the world's most dangerous game.

programme.title: Turbo
programme.desc: A high velocity comedy about an underdog snail who kicks into overdrive when he miraculously attains the power of super-speed. But after making fast friends with a crew of streetwise, tricked-out es-car-goes, Turbo learns that no one succeeds on their own. So he puts his heart and shell on the line to help his pals achieve their dreams, before Turbo-charging his own impossible dream: winning the Indy 500.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda
programme.desc: Clumsy and overweight panda, Po, dreams of becoming a kung fu master.

programme.title: Shrek 2
programme.desc: Happily ever after will have to wait as Shrek, Princess Fiona, and Donkey visit the in-laws. Outraged that Fiona has wed an ogre, the King hires hit man Puss in Boots to make the problem disappear.

programme.title: Mr. Bean's Holiday
programme.desc: Mr Bean can't believe his luck when he wins a camcorder and an all-expense paid holiday to the French Riviera. But during his journey to the south, he falls face first into a series of mishaps.

programme.title: An American Tail: Fievel Goes West
programme.desc: Lured out west by the crafty Cat R. Waul, Fievel joins forces with famed lawdog Wylie Blurp to thwart a sinister plot to transform unsuspecting settlers into mouse burgers!

programme.title: Trolls
programme.desc: When Troll Village is invaded by the Bergens, two mismatched trolls must try and tolerate each other as they set out on a journey to rescue their friends.

programme.title: A Boy Called Christmas
programme.desc: In this origin story of Father Christmas, an ordinary boy (with a loyal pet mouse and a reindeer at his side) sets out on an extraordinary adventure to find his father who is on a quest to discover the fabled village of Elfhelm.

programme.title: The Flintstones
programme.desc: Travel back to the stone-age in this big-budget treatment of the world's favourite prehistoric family! Fred Flintstone, a put-upon blue-collar worker struggling to squeak by, with the help of his best buddy Barney and his wife Wilma. After an aptitude test mix up, Fred Flintstone trades his job as Slate & Company Bronto-crane operator for a vice presidency. But there's trouble brewing in Bedrock: An evil executive and his sinister secretary are now plotting to use Fred as the fall guy in an embezzlement scheme!

programme.title: The Angry Birds Movie
programme.desc: In this hilarious animated adventure comedy, you'll finally find out why the birds are so angry. In an island paradise populated entirely by happy, flightless birds - or almost entirely, Red, a bird with a temper problem, speedy Chuck, and the volatile Bomb have always been outsiders. But when the island is visited by mysterious green piggies, it's up to these unlikely outcasts to figure out what the pigs are up to.

programme.title: Sinbad: Legend of the Seven Seas
programme.desc: It's high-seas adventure when legendary swashbuckler Sinbad, his loyal pooch Spike, and the daring Princess Marina face off against the trickster Goddess of Chaos and her mischievous monsters.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda 3
programme.desc: When Po's long-lost panda father suddenly reappears, the reunited duo travels to a secret panda paradise to meet scores of hilarious new panda characters. When the supernatural villain Kai begins to sweep across China defeating all the kung fu masters, Po must do the impossible: learn to train a village full of his fun-loving, clumsy brethren to become the ultimate band of kung fu pandas.

programme.title: Babe
programme.desc: The inspirational story of a shy Yorkshire piglet who doesn't quite know his place in the world. But when Farmer Hoggett wins him at the county fair, Babe discovers that he can be anything he wants to be - even an award-winning sheepdog. With the help of a delightful assortment of barnyard friends, the heroic little pig is headed for the challenge of his life in this endearing and fun-filled tale the whole family will love.

programme.title: The Boss Baby: Family Business
programme.desc: Boss Baby continues to navigate the cutthroat corporate jungle gym of Baby Corp, while angling to achieve the near-impossible: the work-life balance of a modern career baby.

programme.title: Over the Hedge
programme.desc: Spring has sprung, and Verne and his woodland friends awaken from their long winter's nap to discover that a large, green hedge has cropped up right through the middle of their once-natural habitat. Enter RJ, an opportunistic raccoon who explains that the world beyond the hedge is 'the gateway to the good life' where peculiar creatures called humans live to eat, rather than eat to live. \.

programme.title: Open Season
programme.desc: A clueless domesticated bear and an outcast deer try to survive trigger-happy hunters and hostile forest critters.

programme.title: Paddington
programme.desc: This film tells the story of the comic misadventures of a young Peruvian bear who travels to the city in search of a home. Finding himself lost and alone, he begins to realise that city life is not all he had imagined until he meets the kindly Brown family who read the label around his neck that says \.

programme.title: Bee Movie
programme.desc: A bee is abuzz over a scandal: people are stealing honey to eat. With the help of a florist, he sues the human race for 'honey laundering'.

programme.title: Trolls World Tour
programme.desc: Poppy and Branch discover that there are six different troll tribes scattered over six different lands. Each tribe is also devoted to six different kinds of music - funk, country, techno, classical, pop and rock. When rockers Queen Barb and King Thrash set out to destroy the other music, Poppy and Branch embark on a daring mission to unite the trolls and save the diverse melodies from becoming extinct.

programme.title: How to Train Your Dragon
programme.desc: Set in the mythical world of burly Vikings and fire-breathing dragons, a Viking teenager takes in an injured dragon and sees an opportunity to set his tribe on a new course.

programme.title: Early Man
programme.desc: Set at the dawn of time when prehistoric creatures roamed the earth, Early Man tells the story of courageous caveman Dug and his sidekick Hognob who, together with their fearless new friend Goona, must unite their Stone Age Tribe against the mighty Bronze Age enemy, Lord Nooth.

programme.title: Wallace & Gromit: Curse Of Were-Rabbit
programme.desc: Wallace and Gromit's latest enterprise is Anti-Pesto, pest control with a heart. When called upon by the dotty Lady Tottington to solve her rabbit infestation, Wallace tangles with her Ladyship's would-be suitor, rotten cad Victor Quartermaine.
